Flatlands Ave., at the S.W. corner of East 107th Street, showing the Chas. P. Vanderveer house; erected by him in 1839.    It was also called the John Vanderveer house.    C.B. Vanderveer occupied it in 1873.
One,Yungling was the owner in 1922. The farm was owned by Jacob Sheendam in 1666. This set consists of three views taken at the same time.
